article.description: Twymond Howard made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 3.1 seconds remaining to help UT Martin beat James Madison 78-75 on Sunday.
article.headline: Howard hits go-ahead 3; UT Martin beats James Madison 78-75
article.linkText: Howard hits go-ahead 3; UT Martin beats James Madison 78-75
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Twymond Howard made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 3.1 seconds remaining to help UT Martin beat James Madison 78-75 on Sunday. It was Howard's first 3 of the season after missing his previous seven. The game was tied three different times in the final three minutes. UT Martin's Jacolby Mobley made a layup to knot it at 71 and, after a James Madison miss, Myles Taylor hit a shot for a two-point lead. Later, Ron Curry made a shot and was fouled, but missed the free throw with 21 seconds left. After Howard heroics, Joey McLean's half-court 3-pointer was off the mark. Mobley led UT Martin (1-4) with 16 points and Chandler Rowe had 14. Howard finished with five points on 2-of-8 shooting. The Skyhawks made 54.5 percent of their shots, including 12 of 27 3-pointers. Curry scored 21 points for James Madison (2-3), which made 11 of 30 shots beyond the arc.
